Program for posting status updates on Facebook.

This program can be used to post status updates on Facebook.
The user credentials and the privacy settings need to be defined in
a file called settings.properties.
This file must exist in the same folder as the jar file itself.

The settings file must contain informations in the following style:
#===============================================================================
# Define the email address of the Facebook account to be used.
User=user@example.com

# Define the password of the Facebook account.
Pass=VerySecret

# Define the Privacy setting of the Status Update to be used.
# Possible values: Public, Friends, Only Me
Privacy=Only Me
#===============================================================================

The message that shall be posted on Facebook needs to be passed as an argument
to the application.
A valid application call looks as follows:
java -jar "The message to be posted on Facebook" 